<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="156">
<taxonomicName authority="Schellenberg, 1803" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Tinearia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tinearia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tinearia</taxonomicName>
Schellenberg, 1803 was treated as a genus by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, R" editor="Beuk, P" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Baetica" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" title="Fauna Europaea Web Service version 2.6.2" url="www.faunaeur.org" year="2004">Wagner (2004)</bibRefCitation>
following 
<bibRefCitation author="Jezek, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" pagination="232 - 241" title="Reinstatement of the genus Tinearia Schellenberg (Diptera, Psychodidae)." volume="74" year="1977">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ježek">Jezek</normalizedToken>
(1977)
</bibRefCitation>
. This species group is undoubtedly monophyletic, however based on morphology and some analyses of molecular data it appears to be deeply nested within 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Psychoda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychoda" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Psychoda</taxonomicName>
s.l. (
<bibRefCitation author="Vaillant, F" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe vaudoise des sciences naturelles" pageId="9" pageNumber="158" pagination="141 - 163" title="Propositions pour une revision de la classification des Dipteres PsychodidaePsychodinae." volume="80" year="1990">Vaillant 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Espindola, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" pagination="489 - 498" title="Phylogenetic relationships in the subfamily Psychodinae (Diptera, Psychodidae)." url="10.1111/j.1463-6409.2012.00544.x" volume="41" year="2012">Espindola et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kvifte, GM" journalOrPublisher="Norwegian Journal of Entomology" pageId="9" pageNumber="158" pagination="108 - 119" title="Moth flies (Diptera, Psychodidae) from Finnmark, northern Norway." url="http://www.entomologi.no/journals/nje/2012-2/pdf/nje-vol59-no2-108-119-kvifte.pdf" volume="59" year="2012">Kvifte and Andersen 2012</bibRefCitation>
, Kvifte unpubl.). Inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schellenberg, 1803" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Tinearia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tinearia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tinearia</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus within 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Psychoda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychoda" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Psychoda</taxonomicName>
would thus allow ease of identification of monophyletic units, whereas recognising 
<taxonomicName authority="Schellenberg, 1803" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Tinearia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tinearia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tinearia</taxonomicName>
as a separate taxon would render 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Psychoda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psychoda" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Psychoda</taxonomicName>
paraphyletic. For a discussion of the monophyly criterion in supraspecific taxonomy, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Komarek, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomological problems" pageId="9" pageNumber="158" pagination="55 - 70" title="Problems in taxonomy and suggestions for a standardized description of new taxa." volume="36" year="2006">Komarek and Beutel (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
